The '''Court of Appeal of Paris''' ({{lang-fr|Cour d'appel de Paris}}) is the largest [[Court of Appeal (France)|appeals court in France]] in terms of the number of [[Legal case|cases]] brought before it.
The Court is housed in the ''[[Palais de Justice, Paris|Palais de Justice]]'' of [[Paris]]. Jacques Degrandi has been the president of the Court since 2010.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.ca-paris.justice.fr/index.php?rubrique=11048&article=19532 | title=Jacques Degrandi, premier président de la cour d'appel de Paris |author= | date=May 19, 2012 | work= | language=French | publisher=Court of Appeal of Paris | accessdate=October 2, 2012 }}</ref>
