A post office operated at the original site of Isabella from 1896 to 1953, then at the relocated site from 1953 until the name was changed to [[Lake Isabella]] in 1957.<ref name=CGN /> The town was founded by Steven Barton in 1893 and named in honor of [[Isabella I of Castile|Queen Isabella]] of Spain while her name was current during the [[1893 Columbian Exposition]].<ref name=CGN />
